## Deploy verification

A healthy attendance deploy returns `"build":"attendance-v1"` from `GET /` and echoes Slack `url_verification` challenges from `POST /api/slack/events`.

## Attendance access

JWT attendance APIs (`/api/eta/*`, `/:lang/v1/attendance/*`) are restricted to roles `admin` and `chief_of_staff`. Frontend should hide the Attendance nav/page for every other role.

## Attendance rules

- Reminders: auto 11:00 AM IST DMs are **disabled** (`AUTO_REMINDERS_ENABLED=false`) until explicitly re-enabled.
- Test DM allowlist: set `ATTENDANCE_DM_ALLOWLIST=abhishek.ghosh1@mastersunion.org` so Slack attendance DMs / WFH manager emails only go to that person; clear the var to restore normal behavior.
- Test reminder buttons: `ATTENDANCE_TEST_EMAIL` ŌĆö sole recipient for `POST /api/eta/test-remind` (FE temp buttons).
- Late submission: posts at/after **11:30 AM IST**.
- User modal: `GET /api/eta/stats/:slackUserId/detail` (approved + unapproved WFH/leave + ETA).
- Set counters: `POST /api/eta/stats/:slackUserId/set-counts` (exact WFH/leave approved/denied/etc; history kept).
- Zero counters: `POST /api/eta/stats/:slackUserId/reset-counts` (history kept).
- Policies (admin/CoS, editable in-app): `GET|PUT /api/eta/policies` ŌĆö markdown leave/WFH/ETA SOP doc. FE: `/attendance/policies`.

## Escalation tracker

- Slack channel: set `SLACK_ESCALATION_CHANNEL_NAME` (default `escalations`) or `SLACK_ESCALATION_CHANNEL_ID`.
- Top-level channel messages = new escalation; thread replies = updates.
- Status inferred from keywords (`resolved`, `in progress`, `waiting`, etc.) + manual override via API.
- **LLM analysis** (`AI_PROVIDER` + `GEMINI_API_KEY` or `ANTHROPIC_API_KEY`): auto-runs on new Slack updates; produces `ai.summary`, `ai.blockers`.
- APIs (same JWT + role gate as attendance):
  - `GET /api/eta/escalations` ŌĆö list with latest context + summary counts
  - `GET /api/eta/escalations/:id` ŌĆö full timeline + AI summary
  - `POST /api/eta/escalations/sync` ŌĆö backfill from Slack (optional `days`, default 30)
  - `POST /api/eta/escalations/:id/analyze` ŌĆö re-run LLM analysis
  - `PATCH /api/eta/escalations/:id/status` ŌĆö manual status change
  - `POST /api/eta/escalations/:id/notes` ŌĆö admin note / update
